                            										<div class="gdlr-core-column-40 gdlr-core-item-pdlr">
                            										<p class="text-justify">
                            											Pharmacognosy is probably the oldest of the modern sciences that involves the study of the physical, chemical, biochemical and biological properties of natural drugs, including the search for new drugs from natural sources. The subject is one of the core branches in the pharmacy curriculum and therefore found an important niche in the Vaageswari College of Pharmacy. It is approved by all the major regulatory bodies in India. There are several ongoing activities, including isolation of bioactive compounds, developing herbal formulations, standardizing herbal raw materials. Department works on phytochemical studies and develops screening methods for natural products.</p>
                            									</div>
                            									</div>
                            									<h5 class="pagehead mt-3">
                            										MICROBIOLOGY AND BIOTECHNOLOGY LABS
                            									</h5>
                            									<div>
                            										<p class="text-justify">
                            											The study of microscopic creatures that cannot be seen with the naked eye is known as microbiology. A microbiologist is a scientist who studies bacteria and other microscopic creatures. This means that microbiology is dedicated to the study of various species including bacteria, fungi, viruses and archaea, as well as parasitic worms, in their habitats. While medical microbiology is mostly concerned with the study of bacteria that are both beneficial and harmful to human and animals, it also include the study of germs that are favorable to human health. Biotechnology deals with methods of changing living organisms according to human needs using rDNA technology and genetic engineering, extending back to the domestication of animals, agriculture, and hybridization.</p>
                            									</div>
